Week 10 (AWS Core: IAM + EC2) ‚Äî this is a super important one because IAM & EC2 are among the most frequently asked AWS interview topics.
By the end of this week, you‚Äôll not only know how to create and secure EC2 instances, but also how to apply IAM best practices (least privilege, MFA, roles, policies).

üìÖ Week 10: AWS IAM + EC2 (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Understand IAM deeply (users, groups, roles, policies, MFA).
- Get comfortable with EC2 (instances, AMIs, key pairs, SSH, security groups).
- Learn to secure and troubleshoot access to EC2.
- Build a Secure EC2 Deployment Project repo.

Day 1 ‚Üí IAM Fundamentals
- Topics:
	- IAM concepts: Users, Groups, Roles.
	- Authentication vs Authorization.
	- IAM Policies ‚Üí JSON structure (Effect, Action, Resource).
	- Inline vs Managed policies.
	- IAM Best Practices: least privilege, no root account usage.
- Practice:
	- Create IAM user with CLI access only.
	- Create IAM group (DevOps) ‚Üí attach policies ‚Üí add users.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è iam_basics.md: Notes + screenshots of IAM setup (users, groups, policies).
- Interview Qs:
	- Difference between IAM user, group, and role?
	- What is the principle of least privilege?

Day 2 ‚Üí IAM Security Best Practices
- Topics:
	- MFA setup for IAM users.
	- Access key rotation.
	- Password policies (complexity, rotation).
	- Service-linked roles.
	- SCP (Service Control Policies, AWS Organizations intro).
- Practice:
	- Enable MFA for an IAM user.
	- Rotate access keys.
	- Apply strict password policy.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è iam_security_pack/ ‚Üí JSON examples of least-privilege policies (S3 read-only, EC2 start/stop).
- Interview Qs:
	- What is MFA and why is it critical?
	- How do you secure IAM access keys?

Day 3 ‚Üí EC2 Basics
- Topics:
	- EC2 instance types (t2.micro, m5.large).
	- AMIs (Amazon Machine Images).
	- Key pairs (for SSH).
	- Security groups (SGs).
	- Elastic IPs.
	- EBS volumes (attach, detach, snapshots).
- Practice:
	- Launch EC2 instance (Ubuntu).
	- Connect via SSH using key pair.
	- Attach/detach EBS volume.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è ec2_basics.md: Step-by-step doc with screenshots ‚Üí Launch & connect to EC2, add volume.
- Interview Qs:
	- What is the difference between AMI and Snapshot?
	- How do you make EC2 SSH more secure?

Day 4 ‚Üí EC2 Security & IAM Integration
- Topics:
	- IAM Roles for EC2 (vs IAM users).
	- Assigning S3 read-only access to EC2 via IAM role.
	- Securing SSH ‚Üí only allow specific IP.
	- Using Systems Manager (SSM) instead of SSH (agent-based access).
- Practice:
	- Create IAM role with S3 read-only policy.
	- Attach role to EC2 ‚Üí test access to S3 without credentials.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è secure_ec2_deployment/ ‚Üí Deploy EC2 + IAM role + SG with restricted SSH.
- Interview Qs:
	- Difference between IAM role and IAM policy?
	- Why prefer IAM roles over embedding keys in EC2?

Day 5 ‚Üí Troubleshooting EC2 & IAM
- Topics:
	- Common issues:
		- EC2 not reachable (SG/NACL misconfig).
		- SSH ‚ÄúPermission denied‚Äù errors.
		- EC2 not starting ‚Üí EBS or limits.
		- IAM policy misconfiguration.
	- Tools: CloudWatch Logs, VPC Flow Logs.
- Practice:
	- Break SSH by removing SG ‚Üí debug & fix.
	- Try IAM user with insufficient policy ‚Üí debug error.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è ec2_troubleshooting_playbook.md: At least 5 issues + fixes.
- Interview Qs:
	- How do you debug ‚ÄúEC2 not reachable‚Äù issue?
	- What‚Äôs the difference between SG and NACL in debugging?

Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Secure EC2 Deployment
- Project ‚Üí Build and document an end-to-end secure EC2 deployment.
- Deliverables:
	- Custom VPC (from Week 8).
	- Public subnet EC2 with restricted SSH (only from your IP).
	- IAM Role ‚Üí EC2 access to S3.
	- Attach EBS volume for data persistence.
	- CloudWatch Alarm ‚Üí CPU > 70%.
- Repo ‚Üí secure-ec2-deployment
	- Terraform/CLI scripts + README + diagram.
- Interview Drill:
	- Walk me through your EC2 project.
	- How do you secure EC2 against brute-force SSH attacks?

Day 7 ‚Üí Weekly Wrap-up + Mock Interview
- Tasks:
	- Push Secure EC2 Deployment Repo to GitHub.
	- Add diagrams (draw.io, Lucidchart).
	- Write blog post ‚Üí ‚ÄúHow to Secure an EC2 Instance in AWS‚Äù.
- Mock Interview:
