Week 11 (AWS S3 + RDS).
This week is all about data storage in AWS ‚Üí S3 (object storage) and RDS (managed relational database).
Interviewers love asking S3 security questions (block public access, encryption) and RDS availability questions (Multi-AZ vs Read Replicas).

üìÖ Week 11: AWS S3 + RDS (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Master AWS S3: storage, policies, encryption, hosting.
- Learn RDS basics: MySQL/Postgres managed databases.
- Build hands-on labs for secure S3 storage and RDS high availability.
- Finish with a Static Website Hosting Project (S3 + CloudFront + RDS integration).

Day 1 ‚Üí S3 Basics
- Topics:
	- What is S3? Buckets, objects, regions.
	- S3 storage classes: Standard, IA, One Zone-IA, Glacier.
	- Object key, versioning, metadata.
	- ACLs vs Bucket Policies.
- Practice:
	- Create S3 bucket ‚Üí upload/download objects.
	- Enable versioning.
	- Delete object ‚Üí restore from previous version.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è s3_basics.md: Notes + screenshots ‚Üí bucket creation, versioning, file uploads.
- Interview Qs:
	- Difference between bucket policy and ACL?
	- What is object versioning in S3?

Day 2 ‚Üí S3 Security & Encryption
- Topics:
	- Block Public Access (BPA).
	- Bucket Policies (JSON examples).
	- Encryption: SSE-S3, SSE-KMS, client-side.
	- Pre-signed URLs.
- Practice:
	- Create private bucket ‚Üí block all public access.
	- Generate pre-signed URL for object.
	- Enable SSE-KMS encryption.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è s3_security_pack/ ‚Üí repo with JSON examples of S3 policies + encryption notes.
- Interview Qs:
	- How do you prevent public S3 access?
	- SSE-S3 vs SSE-KMS ‚Üí difference?

Day 3 ‚Üí Static Website Hosting with S3
- Topics:
	- Static website hosting (HTML/JS/CSS).
	- Index & error documents.
	- CloudFront integration (CDN).
	- Logging & monitoring with CloudWatch.
- Practice:
	- Host static website on S3.
	- Add CloudFront distribution.
	- Enable HTTPS with ACM certificate.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è s3_static_website/ ‚Üí repo with index.html + hosting config + CloudFront setup.
- Interview Qs:
	- How do you secure a static website hosted on S3?
	- What‚Äôs the role of CloudFront with S3?

Day 4 ‚Üí RDS Basics
- Topics:
	- What is RDS? Supported engines (MySQL, PostgreSQL, MariaDB, Oracle, SQL Server, Aurora).
	- Instance classes, storage types.
	- Security: SGs, encryption, backups.
	- Parameter Groups & Option Groups.
- Practice:
	- Launch RDS MySQL instance.
	- Connect from EC2 (private subnet).
	- Run queries: create DB, tables, insert/select data.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è rds_basics.md: Setup + SQL script (table creation + data insert).
- Interview Qs:
	- Difference between RDS and DynamoDB?
	- How do you secure RDS access?

Day 5 ‚Üí RDS High Availability & Security
- Topics:
	- Multi-AZ deployment vs Read Replicas.
	- Backup & Restore.
	- Performance Insights.
	- IAM authentication for RDS.
- Practice:
	- Enable Multi-AZ RDS MySQL.
	- Create Read Replica.
	- Simulate failover ‚Üí observe new primary.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è rds_ha_demo/ ‚Üí doc + screenshots ‚Üí failover test + read replica setup.
- Interview Qs:
	- Multi-AZ vs Read Replica ‚Üí difference?
	- How do you troubleshoot RDS connection issues?

Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Static Website + Database
- Project ‚Üí Deploy a mini web app with S3 + RDS backend.
- Deliverables:
	- S3 static site (frontend).
	- RDS MySQL DB (backend).
