Week 12 (AWS Monitoring with CloudWatch).
This week is all about observability inside AWS ‚Üí metrics, logs, alarms, dashboards.
Interviewers will often test your ability to detect and troubleshoot issues in AWS workloads (EC2 CPU spike, S3 access issues, RDS high latency).

üìÖ Week 12: AWS Monitoring with CloudWatch (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Understand CloudWatch metrics, logs, and alarms.
- Learn log collection, filtering, and insights.
- Build a monitoring + alerting setup for EC2 & RDS.
- End with a Monitoring Capstone Project ‚Üí a mini monitoring stack inside AWS.

Day 1 ‚Üí CloudWatch Metrics
- Topics:
	- AWS service metrics ‚Üí EC2 (CPU, Disk, Network), RDS, S3, ELB.
	- Dimensions & namespaces (AWS/EC2, AWS/RDS).
	- Custom metrics (push own metrics via CLI/SDK).
- Practice:
	- Launch EC2 ‚Üí check CPU, network metrics in CloudWatch.
	- Publish custom metric ‚Üí aws cloudwatch put-metric-data.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è cw_metrics_demo/ ‚Üí script that pushes custom metric ‚ÄúDiskUsage%‚Äù every minute.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between standard and detailed monitoring in EC2?
	- How do you create a custom CloudWatch metric?

Day 2 ‚Üí CloudWatch Alarms
- Topics:
	- Alarm states ‚Üí OK, ALARM, INSUFFICIENT_DATA.
	- Thresholds (static vs anomaly detection).
	- Alarm actions ‚Üí SNS notification, Auto Scaling, Lambda trigger.
- Practice:
	- Create alarm ‚Üí EC2 CPU > 70% for 5 minutes.
	- Link alarm to SNS topic ‚Üí email alert.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è cw_alarms_demo/ ‚Üí Terraform/CLI setup for EC2 + alarm + SNS.
- Interview Qs:
	- What happens when an alarm goes into ALARM state?
	- How can CloudWatch alarms trigger Auto Scaling?

Day 3 ‚Üí CloudWatch Logs
- Topics:
	- Log groups & log streams.
	- Log agents (CloudWatch Agent, Fluent Bit).
	- Filters & subscription filters.
	- Log retention policies.
- Practice:
	- Install CloudWatch Agent on EC2 ‚Üí send logs to CloudWatch.
	- Create metric filter ‚Üí count ‚ÄúERROR‚Äù logs.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è cw_logs_demo/ ‚Üí EC2 app sending logs to CloudWatch + ERROR filter.
- Interview Qs:
	- Difference between CloudWatch Logs vs Metrics?
	- How do you send app logs to CloudWatch?

Day 4 ‚Üí CloudWatch Insights & Dashboards
- Topics:
	- CloudWatch Logs Insights (query language).
	- Create dashboards ‚Üí multiple widgets (CPU, memory, custom metric).
	- Cross-service metrics (EC2 + RDS + ELB on one dashboard).
- Practice:
	- Query logs with Insights: fields @timestamp, @message | filter @message like /ERROR/.
	- Build dashboard ‚Üí EC2 CPU + RDS Latency.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è cw_dashboard_demo/ ‚Üí Dashboard JSON export + screenshots.
- Interview Qs:
	- How do you build a dashboard for EC2 + RDS?
	- How is CloudWatch Insights different from Athena?

Day 5 ‚Üí CloudTrail & Monitoring Security
- Topics:
	- CloudTrail basics: API activity logging.
	- CloudTrail ‚Üí CloudWatch integration.
	- Detect suspicious actions (e.g., DeleteBucket, CreateUser).
	- GuardDuty intro ‚Üí threat detection.
- Practice:
	- Enable CloudTrail in AWS account.
	- Send CloudTrail logs to CloudWatch ‚Üí create alert for DeleteBucket.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è cloudtrail_alert_demo/ ‚Üí detect suspicious activity (IAM change, bucket delete).
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between CloudWatch and CloudTrail?
	- How do you detect unauthorized API activity?

Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: AWS Monitoring Setup
- Project ‚Üí ‚ÄúAWS Monitoring Pack‚Äù
- Deliverables:
	- EC2 + RDS monitored with CloudWatch metrics.
	- Custom alarm (CPU > 70%, RDS Latency > 200ms).
	- CloudWatch Agent ‚Üí app logs to CloudWatch.
	- Dashboard ‚Üí EC2 + RDS + custom metric.
	- SNS ‚Üí email alert on alarm trigger.
- Repo ‚Üí aws-monitoring-project
	- Terraform/CLI configs + dashboard JSON + README.
- Interview Drill:
	- Walk me through your monitoring project.
	- How do you differentiate between CloudWatch, CloudTrail, and GuardDuty?

Day 7 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mock Interview
- Tasks:
	- Push repos ‚Üí cw_metrics_demo, cw_alarms_demo, cw_logs_demo, cw_dashboard_demo, cloudtrail_alert_demo, aws-monitoring-project.
	- Document ‚ÄúAWS Monitoring Cheatsheet‚Äù ‚Üí metrics, alarms, logs, dashboards.
	- Blog post ‚Üí ‚ÄúSetting up Monitoring & Alerts in AWS CloudWatch‚Äù.
- Mock Interview:
	- How do you monitor EC2 & RDS?
	- Walk me through CloudWatch Logs ‚Üí Insights workflow.
	- How do you detect malicious IAM activity?

‚úÖ End of Week 12 Deliverables
- 5‚Äì6 repos/demos ‚Üí metrics, alarms, logs, dashboards, security alerts.
- 1 polished AWS Monitoring Project (portfolio-ready).
- Deep confidence in AWS observability & monitoring.

