Month 4 (Phase 2 ‚Üí DevOps Core).
Week 13 = Terraform Basics (IaC foundations). This is where you‚Äôll shift from AWS Console clicks ‚Üí to infrastructure as code.
Here‚Äôs your Week 13 Daily-Level Roadmap:

üìÖ Week 13: Terraform Basics (5 Days)
üéØ Goal
- Understand Infrastructure as Code (IaC) and why it matters.
- Learn Terraform workflow: init, plan, apply, destroy.
- Deploy AWS infra (EC2, S3, IAM) using Terraform.
- Push your first Terraform AWS Infra Repo to GitHub.

Day 1 ‚Üí IaC & Terraform Fundamentals
Topics:
- What is IaC? (Terraform vs CloudFormation vs Ansible).
- Terraform basics: Providers, Resources, State file.
- Terraform Workflow: terraform init, plan, apply, destroy.
Practice:
- Install Terraform on local system.
- Configure AWS provider (provider "aws" { region = "us-east-1" }).
- Write first Terraform config ‚Üí create S3 bucket.
Mini-Project:
‚û°Ô∏è tf-s3-basic/ ‚Üí Terraform config that provisions an S3 bucket.
Interview Qs:
- Difference between IaC and manual infra setup?
- What‚Äôs the purpose of terraform.tfstate file?

Day 2 ‚Üí Variables & Outputs
Topics:
- Input variables (variable block).
- Default values & variable types.
- Outputs (output block) ‚Üí expose useful info.
- .tfvars file for variable assignment.
Practice:
- Create Terraform config for EC2 instance.
- Pass instance type via variable.
- Output EC2 public IP after deployment.
Mini-Project:
‚û°Ô∏è tf-ec2-with-vars/ ‚Üí Deploy EC2 instance with variables & outputs.
Interview Qs:
- What‚Äôs the difference between terraform.tfvars and environment variables?
- Why use outputs in Terraform?

Day 3 ‚Üí Providers & Resource Dependencies
Topics:
- Provider plugins (AWS, Azure, GCP).
- Multiple resources (VPC + Subnet + EC2).
- Dependencies (depends_on).
- Resource naming conventions.
Practice:
- Deploy VPC + Subnet + EC2 in single Terraform config.
- Use depends_on to control order.
Mini-Project:
‚û°Ô∏è tf-vpc-ec2/ ‚Üí One config that provisions VPC ‚Üí Subnet ‚Üí EC2.
Interview Qs:
- How does Terraform know which order to create resources?
- What‚Äôs the difference between explicit and implicit dependencies?

Day 4 ‚Üí State Management
Topics:
- Local state (terraform.tfstate).
- Refreshing state (terraform refresh).
- Drift detection (infra changed outside Terraform).
- Locking state (why it‚Äôs needed in teams).
Practice:
- Create EC2 manually in AWS Console.
- Run terraform plan ‚Üí detect drift.
- Run terraform import ‚Üí bring existing resource into Terraform.
Mini-Project:
‚û°Ô∏è tf-state-lab/ ‚Üí Experiment repo showing drift detection + import.
Interview Qs:
- What happens if you delete a resource outside Terraform?
- How do you manage state files in a team?

Day 5 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mini-Capstone
Capstone Project:
‚û°Ô∏è ‚ÄúTerraform AWS Infra‚Äù
- VPC (10.0.0.0/16).
- Public EC2 instance (t2.micro).
- S3 bucket for logs.
- IAM role for EC2 (S3 read-only).
Deliverables:
- GitHub Repo ‚Üí terraform-aws-infra
	- Terraform configs (.tf files).
	- README ‚Üí setup steps + diagram.
	- .gitignore (ignore .terraform/, *.tfstate).
Mock Interview:
- Walk me through your Terraform project.
- What are the risks of committing .tfstate to GitHub?

‚úÖ End of Week 13 Deliverables
- 4 small labs (S3, EC2, VPC, State).
- 1 polished repo: Terraform AWS Infra.
- Confidence in Terraform basics + workflow ‚Üí ready for advanced Terraform (Modules, Workspaces) in Week 14.

Week 14 (Terraform Intermediate).
This builds directly on Week 13 (Terraform Basics) ‚Äî now we‚Äôll dive deeper into modules, workspaces, state management, remote backends, and lifecycle rules. These are the exact areas interviewers and real projects care about when working in teams.

üìÖ Week 14: Terraform Intermediate (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Move from ‚Äúbasic IaC user‚Äù to team-ready Terraform engineer.
- Learn modules, workspaces, remote state, lifecycle rules, and provisioners.
- Build reusable Terraform code and set up infra with proper state management.

Day 1 ‚Üí Terraform Modules (Reusable Infra Blocks)
- Topics:
	- What are modules?
	- Module structure (main.tf, variables.tf, outputs.tf).
	- Using public modules (Terraform Registry).
	- Creating custom modules for EC2, S3, VPC.
- Practice:
	- Use official VPC module from Terraform Registry.
	- Build your own ‚ÄúEC2 Module‚Äù ‚Üí takes AMI, instance type as variables.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è terraform-modules-lab/ ‚Üí Create ec2_module and s3_module ‚Üí deploy both in one root config.
- Interview Qs:
	- What are Terraform modules, and why are they useful?
	- Difference between root module and child module?

Day 2 ‚Üí Workspaces & Environments
- Topics:
	- Workspaces (default, dev, staging, prod).
	- How workspaces manage multiple environments.
	- Environment-specific variables (dev.tfvars, prod.tfvars).
- Practice:
	- Create dev and prod workspaces.
	- Deploy same infra with different variables (t2.micro in dev, t3.medium in prod).
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è terraform-environments/ ‚Üí Deploy same VPC + EC2 in dev & prod using workspaces.
- Interview Qs:
	- Workspaces vs separate repos?
	- How do you manage environment-specific configs in Terraform?

Day 3 ‚Üí Remote State Management
- Topics:
	- State file issues in teams.
	- Remote state backends: S3, GCS, Azure Blob.
	- State locking with DynamoDB (for S3 backend).
	- Security of state files (don‚Äôt store secrets in plain text).
- Practice:
	- Configure remote backend ‚Üí S3 bucket + DynamoDB for locking.
	- Run terraform plan from two terminals to test locking.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è terraform-remote-state/ ‚Üí Setup S3 backend with DynamoDB lock + secure bucket policies.
- Interview Qs:
	- Why is Terraform state important?
	- How do you avoid state file conflicts in teams?

Day 4 ‚Üí Data Sources & Outputs
- Topics:
	- Terraform data sources ‚Üí query existing AWS resources.
	- Output values ‚Üí share infra data between modules.
	- Example: Get latest AMI ID via data source.
- Practice:
	- Use data "aws_ami" to fetch latest Ubuntu AMI.
	- Output VPC ID and EC2 public IP.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è terraform-data-outputs/ ‚Üí Deploy infra that fetches AMI dynamically + outputs useful info.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between variables and data sources?
	- How do outputs help in multi-team projects?

Day 5 ‚Üí Lifecycle Rules & Provisioners
- Topics:
	- Lifecycle rules ‚Üí create_before_destroy, prevent_destroy, ignore_changes.
	- When to use provisioners (local-exec, remote-exec).
	- Why provisioners should be avoided for production.
- Practice:
	- Create EC2 with create_before_destroy.
	- Test ignore_changes by modifying tag manually.
	- Use remote-exec ‚Üí run a shell command on EC2 after provisioning.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è terraform-lifecycle-provisioners/ ‚Üí Repo showing lifecycle rules + example provisioner.
- Interview Qs:
	- What is create_before_destroy used for?
	- Why are provisioners discouraged in Terraform best practices?

Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone: Terraform VPC Setup
- Project ‚Üí Reusable VPC Deployment with Remote State
- Deliverables:
	- VPC with public + private subnets.
	- NAT Gateway + IGW.
	- EC2 instance in private subnet with Bastion access.
	- Remote state stored in S3 with DynamoDB lock.
	- Modules for VPC + EC2.
- Repo ‚Üí terraform-vpc-setup/
	- Modules (vpc_module, ec2_module).
	- Backend config (S3 + DynamoDB).
	- dev.tfvars, prod.tfvars.
	- README + diagram.
- Interview Drill:
	- Walk me through your Terraform VPC project.
	- How do you manage Terraform state in teams?

Day 7 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mock Interview
- Tasks:
	- Push repos ‚Üí terraform-modules-lab, terraform-environments, terraform-remote-state, terraform-vpc-setup.
	- Write blog post ‚Üí ‚ÄúTerraform Remote State & Modules: From Basics to Team-Ready‚Äù.
- Mock Interview:
	- How do you manage Terraform for multiple environments?
	- When do you use ignore_changes in Terraform?
	- What are security risks in Terraform state files?

‚úÖ End of Week 14 Deliverables
- 4‚Äì5 repos: modules, workspaces, remote state, lifecycle rules.
- 1 polished Terraform VPC Setup repo.
- Strong grasp of team-ready Terraform concepts ‚Üí exactly what recruiters test.

Week 15 (Jenkins Basics).
This week is your entry point to CI/CD pipelines, one of the most important skills in DevOps interviews. By the end of this week, you‚Äôll have a working Jenkins setup that builds and tests apps automatically ‚Üí the start of your CI/CD portfolio.

üìÖ Week 15: Jenkins Basics (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Understand Jenkins architecture, installation, and pipeline basics.
- Learn Jenkins jobs (freestyle vs pipeline) and GitHub integration.
- Build your first Jenkins CI pipeline with GitHub.

Day 1 ‚Üí Jenkins Fundamentals
- Topics:
	- What is CI/CD? Why Jenkins?
	- Jenkins architecture: Master vs Agents.
	- Installation ‚Üí on AWS EC2 (Ubuntu).
	- Web interface, plugins, jobs overview.
- Practice:
	- Install Jenkins on EC2.
	- Configure admin user + basic security.
	- Explore plugin manager.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è jenkins_setup.md ‚Üí Step-by-step notes + screenshots of Jenkins running on EC2.
- Interview Qs:
	- What is the difference between Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment?
	- Jenkins Master vs Agent ‚Üí what‚Äôs the difference?

Day 2 ‚Üí Jenkins Jobs (Freestyle)
- Topics:
	- Jenkins Freestyle jobs.
	- Build triggers: manual, SCM polling, cron, webhooks.
	- Build steps: shell commands, build tools (Maven, Gradle).
	- Post-build actions (archive artifacts, email notification).
- Practice:
	- Create freestyle job ‚Üí run echo "Hello Jenkins".
	- Configure SCM trigger ‚Üí job runs on GitHub push.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è jenkins-freestyle-demo/ ‚Üí Job that builds a simple Python/Java app, archives artifacts.
- Interview Qs:
	- When do you use freestyle jobs instead of pipeline?
	- What are common Jenkins job triggers?

Day 3 ‚Üí Jenkins Pipelines (Declarative)
- Topics:
	- What is a Jenkinsfile? Declarative pipeline syntax.
	- Stages & steps ‚Üí build, test, deploy.
	- Groovy basics (used in Jenkins pipelines).
- Practice:
	- Create Jenkins pipeline job.
	- Write simple Jenkinsfile ‚Üí stages: ‚ÄúBuild‚Äù + ‚ÄúTest‚Äù.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è ci-pipeline-demo/ ‚Üí Repo with Jenkinsfile that compiles code + runs unit tests.
- Interview Qs:
	- Difference between Jenkins freestyle and pipeline?
	- What are the advantages of Jenkinsfile-based pipelines?

Day 4 ‚Üí GitHub Integration & Webhooks
- Topics:
	- GitHub ‚Üí Jenkins integration.
	- Git plugin, GitHub plugin.
	- Webhooks for automatic builds on push.
	- Multi-branch pipelines (different branches ‚Üí different pipelines).
- Practice:
	- Connect Jenkins with GitHub repo.
	- Configure webhook ‚Üí push commit ‚Üí Jenkins build triggers automatically.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è github-ci-demo/ ‚Üí Repo with Jenkinsfile + webhook integration.
- Interview Qs:
	- How does Jenkins integrate with GitHub?
	- What‚Äôs a multi-branch pipeline?

Day 5 ‚Üí Jenkins Plugins & Best Practices
- Topics:
	- Common plugins: Git, Pipeline, Blue Ocean, Credentials, Email.
	- Using credentials in Jenkins securely.
	- Jenkins best practices:
		- Store pipeline as code (Jenkinsfile).
		- Don‚Äôt hardcode secrets ‚Üí use credentials manager.
		- Keep Jenkins minimal ‚Üí avoid plugin overload.
- Practice:
	- Install Blue Ocean plugin ‚Üí visualize pipelines.
	- Store GitHub credentials securely in Jenkins ‚Üí use in pipeline.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è jenkins-best-practices.md ‚Üí Document + screenshots of Blue Ocean pipeline view.
- Interview Qs:
	- How do you handle secrets in Jenkins?
	- Why avoid too many plugins in Jenkins?

Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone: CI/CD Hello World
- Project ‚Üí CI/CD Pipeline for a Simple App
- Deliverables:
	- Repo with a Python/Java app.
	- Jenkinsfile with stages: Checkout ‚Üí Build ‚Üí Test ‚Üí Archive Artifact.
	- GitHub integration (webhook).
	- Jenkins job triggers automatically on push.
- Repo ‚Üí ci-cd-hello-world/
	- Code + Jenkinsfile + README.
- Interview Drill:
	- Walk me through your Jenkins CI pipeline.
	- How does Jenkins trigger builds from GitHub?

Day 7 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mock Interview
- Tasks:
	- Push repos ‚Üí jenkins-freestyle-demo, ci-pipeline-demo, github-ci-demo, ci-cd-hello-world.
	- Write blog post ‚Üí ‚ÄúHow I Built My First CI/CD Pipeline with Jenkins‚Äù.
- Mock Interview:
	- Jenkins freestyle vs pipeline ‚Üí when to use each?
	- What are best practices for managing Jenkins jobs?
	- How do you troubleshoot a failing Jenkins job?

‚úÖ End of Week 15 Deliverables
- 3‚Äì4 small repos (freestyle demo, pipeline demo, GitHub CI).
- 1 polished CI/CD Hello World repo.
- Confidence in Jenkins basics ‚Üí jobs, pipelines, GitHub integration.
- Strong interview readiness for CI/CD basics.

Week 16 (Jenkins Advanced).
This week is all about taking Jenkins pipelines to the next level: multi-branch pipelines, artifact management, scaling Jenkins with agents, handling secrets, and advanced troubleshooting. By the end, you‚Äôll be building pipelines that feel like what real teams use in production.

üìÖ Week 16: Jenkins Advanced (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Learn multi-branch pipelines and GitHub PR builds.
- Manage secrets, credentials, and artifacts securely.
- Understand Jenkins agents & scaling.
- Troubleshoot builds effectively.
- Deliver a CI/CD with Artifacts project repo.

Day 1 ‚Üí Multi-Branch Pipelines
- Topics:
	- Multi-branch pipeline concept ‚Üí Jenkins auto-discovers branches with Jenkinsfile.
	- Branch indexing, PR builds.
	- GitHub + Jenkins ‚Üí build every branch automatically.
- Practice:
	- Create repo with 2 branches ‚Üí feature + main.
	- Configure Jenkins multi-branch pipeline ‚Üí detect both branches.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è multi-branch-demo/ ‚Üí Jenkins setup for auto-building all repo branches.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs a multi-branch pipeline in Jenkins?
	- How do you configure Jenkins to build PRs?

Day 2 ‚Üí Credentials & Secrets Management
- Topics:
	- Jenkins Credentials Manager.
	- Types of credentials: username/password, SSH key, AWS tokens, secret text.
	- Injecting credentials into pipelines.
	- Avoiding hardcoded secrets.
- Practice:
	- Store GitHub token in Jenkins.
	- Use credentials in Jenkinsfile with withCredentials.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è secure-pipeline-demo/ ‚Üí Jenkins pipeline that clones private repo using stored credentials.
- Interview Qs:
	- Why should you never hardcode secrets in Jenkinsfile?
	- How do you use credentials in a pipeline securely?

Day 3 ‚Üí Artifact Storage & Publishing
- Topics:
	- What are build artifacts?
	- Storing artifacts ‚Üí Jenkins workspace vs external storage.
	- Artifact management with S3, Nexus, Artifactory.
	- Jenkinsfile ‚Üí archiveArtifacts step.
- Practice:
	- Create pipeline ‚Üí build + archive JAR/ZIP.
	- Upload artifact to S3 bucket.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è artifact-pipeline-demo/ ‚Üí Jenkinsfile ‚Üí build app ‚Üí archive artifact ‚Üí push to S3.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between artifact and artifact repository?
	- How do you store artifacts in Jenkins?

Day 4 ‚Üí Jenkins Agents & Scaling
- Topics:
	- Jenkins master-agent architecture.
	- Types of agents: static, dynamic (cloud-based).
	- Connecting EC2 as Jenkins agent.
	- Docker-based Jenkins agents.
- Practice:
	- Set up an EC2 agent ‚Üí run pipeline on agent node.
	- Configure agent labels ‚Üí specific jobs run on specific nodes.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è jenkins-agent-lab/ ‚Üí Docs/screenshots: pipeline running on AWS EC2 agent.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between Jenkins master and agent?
	- Why use Jenkins agents in production?

Day 5 ‚Üí Pipeline Best Practices & Troubleshooting
- Topics:
	- Jenkinsfile best practices:
		- Always use stages.
		- Fail fast ‚Üí stop early if build fails.
		- Post actions (always, success, failure).
		- Reusable shared libraries (intro).
	- Troubleshooting Jenkins:
		- Checking Jenkins logs.
		- Common errors: plugin conflicts, credential issues, workspace cleanup.
- Practice:
	- Break pipeline intentionally (invalid Git repo URL).
	- Debug using logs + re-run.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è jenkins-troubleshooting-playbook.md ‚Üí 5 common Jenkins errors + solutions.
- Interview Qs:
	- How do you debug a failing Jenkins build?
	- What are best practices for Jenkins pipelines?

Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: CI/CD with Artifacts
- Project ‚Üí Build realistic Jenkins CI/CD pipeline with artifact publishing.
- Deliverables:
	- Jenkinsfile ‚Üí stages: Checkout ‚Üí Build ‚Üí Test ‚Üí Archive ‚Üí Publish to S3/Nexus.
	- Multi-branch pipeline ‚Üí builds all branches.
	- Credentials manager ‚Üí store GitHub + AWS secrets.
	- Run build on Jenkins agent (EC2/Docker).
- Repo ‚Üí ci-cd-with-artifacts/
	- Jenkinsfile + configs + README + diagrams.
- Interview Drill:
	- Walk me through your CI/CD pipeline.
	- How do you handle secrets & artifacts in Jenkins?

Day 7 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mock Interview
- Tasks:
	- Push repos ‚Üí multi-branch-demo, secure-pipeline-demo, artifact-pipeline-demo, jenkins-agent-lab, ci-cd-with-artifacts.
	- Write blog ‚Üí ‚ÄúJenkins Advanced Pipelines with Artifacts & Agents‚Äù.
- Mock Interview:
	- Jenkins credentials vs secrets ‚Üí differences?
	- Jenkins master-agent ‚Üí why do we need it?
	- How do you scale Jenkins for a large team?

‚úÖ End of Week 16 Deliverables
- 4 mini projects ‚Üí multi-branch, credentials demo, artifact pipeline, agent lab.
- 1 polished repo ‚Üí CI/CD with Artifacts.
- Docs ‚Üí Jenkins troubleshooting playbook.
- Confidence with advanced Jenkins (enough for real interviews).


 
Docker ‚Äî the containerization foundation for Kubernetes.
Week 17 will take you from zero ‚Üí building + running containerized apps. You‚Äôll learn images, containers, Dockerfiles, and networking.

üìÖ Week 17: Docker Basics (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Understand containers vs VMs.
- Learn Docker architecture and core commands.
- Build Dockerfiles and run containers.
- Work with Docker networking and volumes.
- End with a Dockerized App Project in your portfolio.

Day 1 ‚Üí Containers vs VMs + Docker Architecture
- Topics:
	- What is a container? Differences from VMs.
	- Docker architecture:
		- Docker Daemon.
		- Docker CLI.
		- Docker Hub/Registry.
	- Images vs Containers.
- Practice:
	- Install Docker (Linux/Windows/Mac).
	- Run your first container: docker run hello-world.
	- Explore: docker ps, docker images, docker info.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è docker_basics.md ‚Üí notes + screenshots of hello-world + architecture diagram.
- Interview Qs:
	- How are containers different from VMs?
	- What is the role of the Docker Daemon?

Day 2 ‚Üí Running & Managing Containers
- Topics:
	- docker run, start, stop, restart, rm.
	- docker exec ‚Üí run commands inside container.
	- Detached vs interactive mode (-d vs -it).
	- Logs: docker logs.
- Practice:
	- Run Ubuntu container ‚Üí enter with bash ‚Üí install curl.
	- Run Nginx container in detached mode ‚Üí test with curl.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è docker_playground/ ‚Üí repo with notes on common container commands.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between docker run and docker start?
	- How do you view logs of a running container?

Day 3 ‚Üí Docker Images & Dockerfile Basics
- Topics:
	- Dockerfile basics: FROM, RUN, CMD, COPY, EXPOSE.
	- Building an image: docker build -t <image-name> ..
	- Image layers & caching.
- Practice:
	- Write Dockerfile for a Python Flask app (hello world).
	- Build image ‚Üí run container ‚Üí access app.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è flask-docker/ ‚Üí simple Flask app with Dockerfile + README.
- Interview Qs:
	- What is the difference between CMD and ENTRYPOINT?
	- How does Docker image caching work?

Day 4 ‚Üí Volumes & Bind Mounts
- Topics:
	- Why persistence is needed ‚Üí containers are ephemeral.
	- Volumes: managed by Docker.
	- Bind mounts: link host directory.
	- Backups using volumes.
- Practice:
	- Run MySQL container with volume ‚Üí verify data persists after container restart.
	- Bind mount local folder ‚Üí container reads/writes to host.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è docker_volumes_demo/ ‚Üí MySQL with persistent volume + README.
- Interview Qs:
	- Difference between volumes and bind mounts?
	- How do you persist data in Docker?

Day 5 ‚Üí Docker Networking Basics
- Topics:
	- Docker networks: bridge, host, none.
	- Exposing ports: -p host:container.
	- Container-to-container networking.
- Practice:
	- Run Nginx on port 8080 ‚Üí access from browser.
	- Run 2 containers (Flask + MySQL) ‚Üí connect over bridge network.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è docker_network_demo/ ‚Üí Flask app talking to MySQL in Docker network.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between bridge and host network?
	- How do two containers talk to each other?

Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Dockerized App
- Project ‚Üí Dockerize a Python Flask web app with persistence + networking.
- Deliverables:
	- Flask app (simple CRUD or Hello World).
	- Dockerfile ‚Üí build app image.
	- Docker Compose (optional intro): Flask + MySQL.
	- Expose app ‚Üí test with curl/browser.
- Repo ‚Üí dockerized-flask-app/
	- Dockerfile, configs, README, diagrams.
- Interview Drill:
	- Walk me through how you Dockerized your app.
	- What are challenges with container persistence?

Day 7 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mock Interview
- Tasks:
	- Push repos ‚Üí docker_playground, flask-docker, docker_volumes_demo, docker_network_demo, dockerized-flask-app.
	- Write blog ‚Üí ‚ÄúMy First Dockerized App with Flask + MySQL‚Äù.
- Mock Interview:
	- What happens when you delete a container vs delete an image?
	- CMD vs ENTRYPOINT in Dockerfile.
	- How do you persist database data in containers?

‚úÖ End of Week 17 Deliverables
- 4 small repos ‚Üí docker playground, Flask app, volumes demo, networking demo.
- 1 capstone repo ‚Üí Dockerized Flask App.
- Deep understanding of images, containers, networking, and persistence.
- Portfolio-ready ‚Üí recruiters love seeing Dockerized apps.

Docker Advanced (Week 18).
Here, you‚Äôll go from single-container basics to multi-container apps with Docker Compose, debugging, private registries, and security scanning ‚Äî this is the ‚Äúreal DevOps‚Äù level recruiters expect.

üìÖ Week 18: Docker Advanced (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Master multi-container orchestration with Docker Compose.
- Debug and monitor containers effectively.
- Use private registries (Harbor, ECR).
- Learn container image security scanning (Trivy).
- End with a Docker Compose Stack Project (Web + DB) in portfolio.

Day 1 ‚Üí Docker Compose Basics
- Topics:
	- Why Compose? ‚Üí managing multi-container apps.
	- docker-compose.yml structure: version, services, volumes, networks.
