	- Write blog ‚Üí ‚ÄúBuilding a Secure Multi-Container App with Docker Compose‚Äù.
- Mock Interview:
	- How do you troubleshoot a container that won‚Äôt start?
	- What‚Äôs the difference between public and private registries?
	- How do you secure Docker images?

‚úÖ End of Week 18 Deliverables
- 4 small repos ‚Üí Compose basics, persistence, debugging, registry demo, Trivy scan.
- 1 capstone repo ‚Üí Secure Docker Compose Stack.
- Hands-on debugging & image security scanning experience.
- Portfolio-level Docker projects ‚Üí recruiters now see you as ‚Äúbeyond fresher"

Week 19 is Kubernetes Basics, which is one of the most crucial turning points in your roadmap.
This is where you move from running containers (Docker) ‚Üí to orchestrating them at scale (K8s).
By the end of this week, you‚Äôll be able to deploy apps into Kubernetes, expose them via services, and manage configs/secrets.

üìÖ Week 19: Kubernetes Basics (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Understand K8s core objects ‚Üí Pods, Deployments, Services, ConfigMaps, Secrets.
- Learn kubectl hands-on.
- Deploy a containerized app into Kubernetes (local cluster: Minikube or kind).
- Build a K8s App Deployment Project repo.

Day 1 ‚Üí Kubernetes Fundamentals
- Topics:
	- What is Kubernetes? ‚Üí container orchestration.
	- Core concepts ‚Üí Pod, Node, Cluster, Control Plane.
	- kubelet, API server, etcd.
- Practice:
	- Install Minikube or kind.
	- Deploy hello-world pod (kubectl run hello-world).
	- View pod (kubectl get pods, kubectl describe pod).
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è k8s-basics.md ‚Üí notes + screenshots of first pod deployment.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between Docker and Kubernetes?
	- What is a Pod in K8s?

Day 2 ‚Üí Pods & Deployments
- Topics:
	- Pods ‚Üí smallest deployable unit.
	- ReplicaSets & Deployments ‚Üí scaling & rolling updates.
	- Commands: kubectl apply -f, kubectl scale, kubectl rollout.
- Practice:
	- Create Deployment ‚Üí Nginx with 3 replicas.
	- Scale replicas up/down.
	- Rollout new version (different image).
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è nginx-deployment.yaml ‚Üí repo with deployment + scaling docs.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between a Pod and Deployment?
	- How do you roll back a Deployment in Kubernetes?

Day 3 ‚Üí Services (ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer)
- Topics:
	- Exposing Pods using Services.
	- Types: ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer.
	- DNS inside K8s (kubectl exec curl).
- Practice:
	- Expose Nginx Deployment via NodePort service.
	- Test app via Minikube service tunnel.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è k8s-service-demo/ ‚Üí deployment + service YAML.
- Interview Qs:
	- Difference between NodePort and LoadBalancer service?
	- How does DNS resolution work inside K8s?

Day 4 ‚Üí ConfigMaps & Secrets
- Topics:
	- Storing configs with ConfigMaps.
	- Storing sensitive data with Secrets (base64 encoded).
	- Mounting as env vars & volumes.
- Practice:
	- Create ConfigMap ‚Üí pass app config.
	- Create Secret ‚Üí DB password.
	- Update Deployment ‚Üí read env vars from Secret.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è k8s-config-secret-demo/ ‚Üí deployment using ConfigMap + Secret.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between ConfigMap and Secret?
	- How do you mount a Secret into a Pod?

Day 5 ‚Üí Debugging Pods & Deployments
- Topics:
	- Debugging commands: kubectl logs, kubectl exec, kubectl describe.
	- Common issues: ImagePullBackOff, CrashLoopBackOff.
	- Troubleshooting methodology.
- Practice:
	- Deploy broken image ‚Üí debug with logs.
	- Fix CrashLoopBackOff by correcting YAML.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è k8s-troubleshooting-playbook.md ‚Üí doc with 5 common pod issues + fixes.
- Interview Qs:
	- How do you debug a CrashLoopBackOff error?
	- What‚Äôs the difference between kubectl logs and kubectl describe?

Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Kubernetes App Deployment
- Project ‚Üí Deploy a Flask app with MySQL in Kubernetes.
	- Deployment for Flask app.
	- Deployment for MySQL DB.
	- Service for each (Flask ‚Üí NodePort, MySQL ‚Üí ClusterIP).
	- ConfigMap for DB config.
	- Secret for DB password.
- Deliverables:
	- Repo: k8s-app-deployment/.
	- YAML files + README + architecture diagram.
- Interview Drill:
	- Walk me through your K8s project.
	- How do ConfigMaps and Secrets work in your deployment?

Day 7 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mock Interview
- Tasks:
	- Push repos ‚Üí nginx-deployment, k8s-service-demo, k8s-config-secret-demo, k8s-app-deployment.
	- Write blog ‚Üí ‚ÄúDeploying My First App in Kubernetes‚Äù.
- Mock Interview:
	- What is the difference between Deployment and StatefulSet?
	- How do you expose a Pod in Kubernetes?
	- What happens if a Pod dies in a Deployment?

‚úÖ End of Week 19 Deliverables
- 3‚Äì4 mini repos (deployment demo, service demo, config/secret demo).
- 1 capstone repo ‚Üí K8s App Deployment.
- Solid understanding of K8s basics ‚Üí Pods, Deployments, Services, ConfigMaps, Secrets.
- Portfolio-ready project + troubleshooting playbook.

Week 20 is where you go deeper into Kubernetes Advanced Concepts.
By now you know how to deploy apps and manage configs, but in this week you‚Äôll learn how to control access, secure workloads, manage resources, and route traffic ‚Äî basically the skills that make you look like a 2-year experienced engineer.

üìÖ Week 20: Kubernetes Advanced (Daily Roadmap)
üéØ Goal
- Learn advanced K8s objects: Ingress, RBAC, Resource Limits, Namespaces.
- Understand scheduling concepts (taints, tolerations, affinity).
- Get hands-on with security controls.
- Build a K8s RBAC + Ingress Demo Project repo.

Day 1 ‚Üí Ingress Controllers & Routing
- Topics:
	- Service exposure recap: ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer.
	- Ingress basics ‚Üí routing external traffic into the cluster.
	- Ingress Controller (NGINX ingress).
	- TLS certificates with Ingress.
- Practice:
	- Install NGINX ingress in Minikube/kind.
	- Deploy two apps ‚Üí configure Ingress to route /app1 and /app2.
	- Enable TLS with self-signed cert.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è k8s-ingress-demo/ ‚Üí multi-app routing + TLS.
- Interview Qs:
	- Difference between LoadBalancer and Ingress?
	- How do you enable HTTPS for an app in K8s?

Day 2 ‚Üí RBAC (Role-Based Access Control)
- Topics:
	- RBAC in Kubernetes ‚Üí Roles, ClusterRoles, RoleBindings, ClusterRoleBindings.
	- ServiceAccounts ‚Üí assigning permissions to pods.
	- Principle of least privilege.
- Practice:
	- Create Role ‚Üí read-only access to pods.
	- Bind Role to user via kubeconfig.
	- Create ServiceAccount ‚Üí assign to a pod.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è k8s-rbac-demo/ ‚Üí YAML files for Role, RoleBinding, ServiceAccount.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between Role and ClusterRole?
	- How do ServiceAccounts differ from IAM roles?

Day 3 ‚Üí Resource Requests & Limits
- Topics:
	- CPU & memory requests vs limits.
	- Quality of Service (QoS) classes ‚Üí Guaranteed, Burstable, BestEffort.
	- Resource quotas at namespace level.
- Practice:
	- Deploy pod with CPU request=100m, limit=200m.
	- Deploy pod without limits ‚Üí observe OOMKill.
	- Create ResourceQuota for a namespace.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è k8s-resource-limits-demo/ ‚Üí YAML for requests, limits, quotas.
- Interview Qs:
	- What happens if a pod exceeds its memory limit?
	- Explain QoS classes in Kubernetes.

Day 4 ‚Üí Namespaces & Multi-Tenancy
- Topics:
	- Namespaces ‚Üí logical separation of workloads.
	- Default vs custom namespaces.
	- Network policies (intro).
	- Resource quotas per namespace.
- Practice:
	- Create two namespaces (dev, prod).
	- Deploy same app in both ‚Üí test isolation.
	- Apply ResourceQuota in prod namespace.
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è k8s-namespaces-demo/ ‚Üí namespace YAML + quota + docs.
- Interview Qs:
	- Why use namespaces in Kubernetes?
	- How do you enforce resource limits across namespaces?

Day 5 ‚Üí Scheduling Basics (Taints, Tolerations, Affinity)
- Topics:
	- Node scheduling basics.
	- Taints & tolerations ‚Üí control which pods run where.
	- Node affinity & pod affinity/anti-affinity.
	- Use cases: DB pods on SSD nodes, separate workloads.
- Practice:
	- Taint a node ‚Üí only allow pods with toleration.
	- Deploy app with node affinity (e.g., label=node=ssd).
	- Deploy pods with anti-affinity (don‚Äôt run on same node).
- Mini-Project:
  
   ‚û°Ô∏è k8s-scheduling-demo/ ‚Üí manifests for taints, tolerations, affinities.
- Interview Qs:
	- What‚Äôs the difference between taints/tolerations and affinity?
	- How do you ensure a DB pod always runs on a specific node?

Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: K8s Advanced Setup
- Project ‚Üí ‚ÄúK8s RBAC + Ingress + Scheduling Demo‚Äù
	- Deploy 2 apps (frontend + backend).
	- Ingress ‚Üí route traffic to both apps.
	- RBAC ‚Üí give read-only access to one namespace.
	- Resource limits ‚Üí restrict CPU/memory.
	- Scheduling ‚Üí backend pod only on SSD node.
- Deliverables:
	- Repo: k8s-advanced-demo/.
	- YAML files, README, architecture diagram.
- Interview Drill:
	- Walk me through your RBAC + Ingress project.
	- How do you enforce least privilege in Kubernetes?

Day 7 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mock Interview
- Tasks:
	- Push repos ‚Üí ingress-demo, rbac-demo, resource-limits-demo, namespaces-demo, scheduling-demo, advanced-demo.
	- Write blog ‚Üí ‚ÄúAdvanced Kubernetes Concepts for DevOps Engineers‚Äù.
- Mock Interview:
	- Explain how Ingress works in Kubernetes.
	- What‚Äôs the difference between Role and ClusterRole?
	- How do you enforce resource usage in a multi-tenant cluster?

‚úÖ End of Week 20 Deliverables
- 4‚Äì5 mini repos ‚Üí Ingress, RBAC, Resource Limits, Scheduling.
- 1 capstone repo ‚Üí Advanced K8s Demo.
- Strong foundation in K8s access control, traffic routing, and resource mgmt.
- Portfolio project ‚Üí Advanced Kubernetes Architecture.
  
  
Week 13 (Terraform Basics) expanded with add-ons as an example first. If this matches your expectations, I‚Äôll do the same expansion for Week 14‚Äì20.

üìÖ Week 13 (Terraform Basics + Add-ons Expanded)
üéØ Goal
- Understand IaC workflow (Terraform init ‚Üí plan ‚Üí apply ‚Üí destroy).
- Deploy AWS infra (EC2, S3, IAM) with Terraform.
