Week 21.
We‚Äôve just completed Terraform, Jenkins, Docker, and Kubernetes (Weeks 13‚Äì20). Now we move into configuration management & GitOps-style automation, starting with Ansible.
This is a crucial phase because:
- You‚Äôll connect infra (Terraform) ‚Üí config (Ansible) ‚Üí apps (Docker/K8s).
- Interviewers often ask Terraform vs Ansible questions.
- Real-world DevOps requires IaC + CM + CI/CD fluency.

üìÖ Week 21: Ansible Basics (Configuration Management Foundations)
üéØ Goal
- Understand why configuration management (CM) is needed.
- Learn Ansible basics ‚Üí inventory, playbooks, ad-hoc commands.
- Automate EC2 configuration (installing Nginx, users, packages).
- Build your first Ansible Infra Automation repo.

üîπ Day 1 ‚Üí Ansible Fundamentals
Topics
- What is Ansible? Why not just Bash?
- Ansible architecture: Control Node vs Managed Nodes.
- SSH-based agentless architecture.
- Inventory (/etc/ansible/hosts).
- Ad-hoc commands.
Practice
- Install Ansible on control node (EC2).
- Create inventory file with 1 EC2 instance.
- Run ad-hoc command: ansible all -m ping.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-setup-lab/ ‚Üí inventory file + ping demo.
Interview Qs
- How does Ansible connect to remote servers?
- Difference between agent-based (Chef, Puppet) vs agentless (Ansible)?

üîπ Day 2 ‚Üí Playbooks & YAML Basics
Topics
- Playbooks structure ‚Üí hosts, tasks, modules.
- Common modules: apt, yum, service, copy, file.
- Idempotency in Ansible.
Practice
- Write playbook ‚Üí install Nginx on EC2.
- Start service, ensure enabled on boot.
- Test idempotency ‚Üí re-run, no changes.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-playbook-nginx/ ‚Üí playbook installs Nginx.
Interview Qs
- What is idempotency in Ansible?
- Difference between ad-hoc command vs playbook?

üîπ Day 3 ‚Üí Variables, Facts, Handlers
Topics
- Variables ‚Üí vars, vars_files.
- Facts ‚Üí system info from hosts.
- Handlers ‚Üí notify + restart services.
Practice
- Playbook ‚Üí deploy Nginx with custom HTML page.
- Use variable for page content.
- Restart Nginx if config changes.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-vars-handlers/ ‚Üí playbook with variables + handlers.
Interview Qs
- What are handlers in Ansible?
- How do you pass variables to playbooks?

üîπ Day 4 ‚Üí Ansible Roles
Topics
- Why roles? ‚Üí reusable structure.
- Role directory layout: tasks/, handlers/, templates/, vars/.
- Using ansible-galaxy init.
Practice
- Convert Nginx playbook ‚Üí Role.
- Use templates/index.html.j2 for dynamic content.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-nginx-role/ ‚Üí reusable role for Nginx.
Interview Qs
- Difference between playbook and role?
- Why use roles in Ansible projects?

üîπ Day 5 ‚Üí Ansible Inventory & Multi-Node Setup
Topics
- Static vs Dynamic inventory.
- AWS EC2 Dynamic Inventory plugin.
- Groups & patterns ([web], [db]).
Practice
- Inventory with 2 groups: web + db.
- Playbook ‚Üí install Apache on web, MySQL on db.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-multi-node/ ‚Üí inventory + playbooks for web/db.
Interview Qs
- Static vs dynamic inventory?
- How does Ansible discover AWS hosts dynamically?

üîπ Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone: Web Server Automation
Project ‚Üí Automate Deployment of Nginx Web Server
- Inventory with 2 EC2 nodes.
- Playbook installs Nginx + custom HTML.
- Role-based structure.
- Handler ‚Üí restart Nginx if config changes.
Deliverables
- Repo ‚Üí ansible-webserver-automation/.
- Includes roles, playbooks, README, screenshots.
Interview Drill
- Walk me through your Ansible automation repo.
- Why use Ansible over Bash scripting?

üîπ Day 7 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mock Interview
Tasks
- Push repos ‚Üí ansible-setup-lab, ansible-playbook-nginx, ansible-vars-handlers, ansible-nginx-role, ansible-multi-node, ansible-webserver-automation.
- Write blog ‚Üí ‚ÄúMy First Ansible Automation Project‚Äù.
Mock Interview
- How does Ansible achieve idempotency?
- Difference between Ansible role vs Terraform module?
- Walk me through how you‚Äôd automate EC2 configuration.

‚úÖ End of Week 21 Deliverables
- 5+ repos (lab, playbooks, role, multi-node, capstone).
- Confidence with Ansible basics ‚Üí inventories, playbooks, roles.
- Portfolio-ready repo: ansible-webserver-automation.
- Ability to compare Terraform vs Ansible in interviews.

‚ö° Add-ons for Week 21 (beyond basics):
- Run Ansible Lint on playbooks.
- STAR Troubleshooting: Playbook fails on one node ‚Üí debug.
- Blog ‚Üí ‚ÄúTerraform vs Ansible: Infra vs Config Management‚Äù.


Week 22 is where you level up in Ansible Advanced.
Here you‚Äôll move beyond single-playbook automation ‚Üí into enterprise-ready practices like Vault (secrets), Templates (Jinja2), Galaxy Roles, Dynamic Inventories, and CI/CD integration with Jenkins/GitHub Actions.
By the end of this week, you‚Äôll be able to design production-ready Ansible automation pipelines and stand out in interviews.

üìÖ Week 22: Ansible Advanced (Secrets, Templates, Galaxy, CI/CD)
üéØ Goal
- Master advanced Ansible features: Vault, Templates, Galaxy Roles.
- Secure playbooks with secrets.
- Work with dynamic inventories (AWS, K8s).
- Integrate Ansible into CI/CD (Jenkins/GitHub Actions).
- Deliver a Config Automation + CI/CD Project for portfolio.

üîπ Day 1 ‚Üí Ansible Vault (Secrets Management)
Topics
- Why secrets management matters.
- Ansible Vault ‚Üí encrypt files (passwords, keys).
- Vault commands: ansible-vault encrypt, decrypt, view, edit.
- Using Vault in playbooks.
Practice
- Encrypt DB password with Vault.
- Use --ask-vault-pass for decryption at runtime.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-vault-demo/ ‚Üí playbook that deploys MySQL using Vault-encrypted root password.
Interview Qs
- What is Ansible Vault?
- How do you secure passwords in Ansible playbooks?

üîπ Day 2 ‚Üí Templates with Jinja2
Topics
- Jinja2 templating ‚Üí {{ variable }}, {% for %}, {% if %}.
- Template module ‚Üí .j2 files.
- Use cases: Config files, dynamic HTML, app configs.
Practice
- Create index.html.j2 ‚Üí dynamic app name + environment.
- Playbook ‚Üí deploy Nginx with template-based page.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-template-demo/ ‚Üí Nginx role with Jinja2 templates.
Interview Qs
- What is Jinja2 used for in Ansible?
- Difference between copy vs template module?

üîπ Day 3 ‚Üí Ansible Galaxy & Reusable Roles
Topics
- What is Ansible Galaxy?
- Import roles from Galaxy (ansible-galaxy install).
- Best practices for role reuse.
- Publishing your own role to Galaxy.
Practice
- Install geerlingguy.mysql role from Galaxy.
- Use it to provision MySQL DB.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-galaxy-lab/ ‚Üí repo with Galaxy role usage + documentation.
Interview Qs
- What‚Äôs the difference between local role and Galaxy role?
- Why is role reuse important?

üîπ Day 4 ‚Üí Dynamic Inventory (AWS & Kubernetes)
Topics
- Static vs Dynamic inventory recap.
- AWS EC2 plugin ‚Üí auto-discover EC2 hosts.
- K8s plugin ‚Üí auto-discover pods/services.
- JSON-based inventory outputs.
Practice
- Configure AWS inventory plugin (aws_ec2.yml).
- Run playbook targeting all EC2 with tag Role=web.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-dynamic-inventory/ ‚Üí AWS EC2 inventory + playbook auto-targets instances.
Interview Qs
- What is a dynamic inventory in Ansible?
- How does Ansible know which hosts to target?

üîπ Day 5 ‚Üí CI/CD with Ansible (Jenkins/GitHub Actions)
Topics
- Why integrate Ansible into pipelines?
- Jenkins pipeline step ‚Üí run Ansible playbook after build.
- GitHub Actions workflow ‚Üí deploy app with Ansible.
Practice
- Jenkinsfile ‚Üí stage ‚ÄúDeploy‚Äù ‚Üí run ansible-playbook site.yml.
- GitHub Actions ‚Üí workflow with ansible/ansible-runner action.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è ansible-cicd-demo/ ‚Üí GitHub Actions workflow that deploys Nginx with Ansible.
Interview Qs
- How do you integrate Ansible into Jenkins?
- Jenkins vs Ansible ‚Üí what‚Äôs the difference in CI/CD?

üîπ Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Secure Config Automation with CI/CD
Project ‚Üí ‚ÄúSecure Ansible + CI/CD Deployment‚Äù
- Features:
	- Multi-node inventory (web + db).
	- Role-based structure.
	- Vault for secrets (DB password).
	- Templates for configs.
	- Galaxy role for DB.
	- CI/CD pipeline ‚Üí Jenkins or GitHub Actions triggers Ansible deploy.
Deliverables
