Patch Add-On Sheet (Weeks 21‚Äì28)
üîπ Week 21‚Äì22 (Ansible: Basics + Advanced)
1. Error Handling & Retries Lab
	- Create playbook that installs a package from a broken repo.
	- Add retries: 3, delay: 10, ignore_errors: yes.
	- Observe failure ‚Üí fix repo ‚Üí rerun playbook.
	- Repo: ansible-error-handling-demo/.
2. Molecule Testing Add-On
	- Install Molecule (pip install molecule[docker]).
	- Test your Nginx role locally with Molecule + Docker.
	- Repo: ansible-role-molecule-tests/.

üîπ Week 23 (Docker + Ansible Integration)
1. Pre-Deployment Image Scan (Trivy)
	- Extend CI/CD pipeline ‚Üí scan Docker image with Trivy before pushing.
	- Fail build on HIGH/Critical CVEs.
	- Repo: ansible-docker-security-pipeline/.
2. Swarm vs K8s Quick Lab
	- Deploy Nginx in Docker Swarm (1 manager, 1 worker).
	- Compare against K8s deployment.
	- Repo: docker-swarm-vs-k8s-notes.md.

üîπ Week 24 (Ansible + K8s + GitOps)
1. Sealed Secrets Lab
	- Install Sealed Secrets controller.
	- Encrypt DB password with kubeseal.
	- Store sealed secret YAML in Git ‚Üí ArgoCD auto-deploys.
	- Repo: gitops-sealed-secrets-demo/.
2. Drift Detection Demo
	- Deploy app via ArgoCD.
	- Manually kubectl edit ‚Üí change replica count.
	- Observe ArgoCD auto-correct drift.
	- Repo: gitops-drift-detection-lab/.

üîπ Week 25 (K8s Production Ops)
1. Autoscaling Lab (HPA)
	- Deploy Flask app ‚Üí expose with Service.
	- Create HPA (kubectl autoscale deployment flask --cpu-percent=50 --min=2 --max=5).
	- Stress test with Apache Benchmark (ab -n 1000 -c 50).
	- Repo: k8s-hpa-demo/.
2. Pod Disruption Budget (PDB)
	- Define PDB: minAvailable: 2 for Flask app.
	- Test rolling updates ‚Üí app always has 2 pods running.
	- Repo: k8s-pdb-demo/.
3. Kustomize vs Helm
	- Deploy same app with both tools.
	- Write blog: ‚ÄúKustomize vs Helm ‚Äì When to Use Each.‚Äù

üîπ Week 26 (K8s Security Foundations)
1. Pod Security Context Lab
	- Create pod with runAsUser: 1000, fsGroup: 2000.
	- Verify permissions with id inside container.
	- Repo: k8s-security-context-demo/.
2. Signed Images with OPA/Gatekeeper
	- Write policy: only allow images signed with Cosign.
	- Deploy unsigned image ‚Üí denied.
	- Repo: k8s-image-signing-policy/.

üîπ Week 27 (CI/CD Security)
1. SBOM (Software Bill of Materials)
	- Use Syft to generate SBOM for Flask app image.
	- Store SBOM as Jenkins artifact.
	- Repo: jenkins-sbom-demo/.
2. Image Signing (Cosign)
	- Sign Docker image with Cosign.
	- Push signed image ‚Üí verify signature in Jenkins pipeline.
	- Repo: jenkins-cosign-demo/.

üîπ Week 28 (K8s Security Advanced)
1. Audit Logs Lab
	- Enable API server audit logs in Minikube.
	- Generate activity (kubectl get pods, create/delete resources).
	- Inspect audit logs.
	- Repo: k8s-audit-logs-lab/.
2. Kyverno Policy Lab
	- Install Kyverno.
	- Write policy: deny pods without resource requests/limits.
	- Compare against Gatekeeper policy.
	- Repo: k8s-kyverno-demo/.
3. Runtime Sandboxing Demo (gVisor)
	- Run Nginx pod with gVisor runtime.
	- Show isolation differences vs default runtime.
	- Repo: k8s-gvisor-sandbox-demo/.

