Week 29, we move into Kubernetes Advanced Networking + Service Mesh (Istio).
This week is all about traffic control, observability, and service-to-service security ‚Äî things recruiters expect from candidates who claim ‚ÄúK8s production experience.‚Äù

üìÖ Week 29: Kubernetes Networking & Service Mesh (Istio Basics)
üéØ Goal
- Go beyond basic K8s networking ‚Üí dive into CNI, Services, Ingress, DNS, and Network Policies.
- Learn Istio Service Mesh for traffic routing, mTLS, and observability.
- Deploy a microservices app with Istio traffic routing + monitoring.

üîπ Day 1 ‚Üí Kubernetes Networking Deep Dive
Topics
- K8s networking model (flat network, every Pod gets IP).
- CNI plugins (Flannel, Calico, Cilium).
- Service discovery & DNS (kube-dns, CoreDNS).
- Service types: ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer recap.
Practice
- Deploy 2 Pods ‚Üí curl using Pod IP + Service name.
- Inspect DNS with kubectl exec busybox -- nslookup <service>.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è k8s-network-basics-demo/ ‚Üí Pod-to-Pod & Pod-to-Service communication demo.
Interview Qs
- How do Pods in different nodes communicate?
- Difference between CNI plugin and Service?

üîπ Day 2 ‚Üí Ingress & Advanced Service Routing
Topics
- Ingress recap (from Week 20).
- Ingress controllers: NGINX, Traefik.
- TLS termination with Ingress.
Practice
- Deploy Nginx Ingress Controller.
- Deploy 2 apps (frontend, backend) ‚Üí route via Ingress:
	- /frontend ‚Üí frontend service.
	- /backend ‚Üí backend service.
- Enable TLS with self-signed cert.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è k8s-ingress-routing-demo/ ‚Üí Multi-app Ingress routing setup.
Interview Qs
- Difference between LoadBalancer and Ingress?
- How do you enable HTTPS for an app in K8s?

üîπ Day 3 ‚Üí Service Mesh Fundamentals
Topics
- What is a Service Mesh? (Control Plane vs Data Plane).
- Why Istio? (traffic mgmt, observability, mTLS).
- Sidecar proxy (Envoy) basics.
Practice
- Install Istio in Minikube (istioctl install).
- Label namespace ‚Üí enable Istio sidecar injection.
- Deploy 2 services ‚Üí confirm sidecar proxies.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è istio-basics-demo/ ‚Üí Install Istio, sidecar injection demo.
Interview Qs
- What is the difference between Ingress and Istio Gateway?
- Why do we need a Service Mesh if K8s already has Services?

üîπ Day 4 ‚Üí Istio Traffic Management
Topics
- Istio VirtualServices & DestinationRules.
- Traffic splitting (blue/green, canary).
- Fault injection (delay, abort).
Practice
- Deploy v1 + v2 of a Flask app.
- Route 90% traffic to v1, 10% to v2.
- Inject 5s delay for testing.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è istio-traffic-routing/ ‚Üí Canary deployment with Istio.
Interview Qs
- How do you implement blue/green deployment in Istio?
- What‚Äôs the difference between VirtualService and Service in K8s?

üîπ Day 5 ‚Üí Istio Security & Observability
Topics
- mTLS (service-to-service encryption).
- Istio AuthorizationPolicies (RBAC at mesh level).
- Observability stack: Prometheus, Grafana, Jaeger, Kiali.
Practice
- Enable mTLS ‚Üí test communication between services.
- Apply AuthorizationPolicy ‚Üí block access from frontend to DB.
- Install Kiali dashboard ‚Üí visualize traffic flow.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è istio-security-observability/ ‚Üí Istio with mTLS + Kiali + Prometheus setup.
Interview Qs
- What is mTLS? How is it different from TLS?
- Which tools does Istio integrate with for monitoring?

üîπ Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Service Mesh Microservices App
Project ‚Üí ‚ÄúK8s Microservices with Istio‚Äù
- Microservices app (Flask frontend + backend + DB).
- Routing: Istio VirtualService ‚Üí route /api to backend.
- Canary release: 80% ‚Üí v1, 20% ‚Üí v2.
- Security: mTLS enabled + AuthorizationPolicy (frontend cannot directly talk to DB).
- Observability: Kiali dashboard ‚Üí visualize service graph.
Deliverables
- Repo ‚Üí k8s-istio-microservices/.
- YAMLs for Istio configs, manifests, screenshots of Kiali.
- README + architecture diagram.
Interview Drill
- Walk me through how Istio handles traffic routing.
- How do you secure service-to-service communication?
- What‚Äôs the role of sidecars in Istio?

üîπ Day 7 ‚Üí Wrap-up + Mock Interview
Tasks
