let‚Äôs continue into Week 31.
By now, you‚Äôve built strong foundations in Kubernetes, CI/CD, Security, and GitOps.
This week, we‚Äôll dive into Cloud-Native Security Tools ‚Üí covering image signing, supply-chain security, policy enforcement, and SBOMs (Software Bill of Materials).
This is a super hot area in 2025 DevSecOps interviews because of software supply-chain attacks (SolarWinds, Log4j). If you can demonstrate knowledge here, you‚Äôll stand out as someone already thinking like a DevSecOps engineer with 2+ years.

üìÖ Week 31: Supply Chain Security & Policy Enforcement
üéØ Goal
- Learn container image signing & verification (Cosign).
- Build SBOMs with Syft/Grype.
- Implement policy-as-code for security compliance.
