Week 32 üöÄ.
At this point, you‚Äôve built strong DevSecOps supply-chain security skills (Cosign, SBOMs, Kyverno). Now, we‚Äôll dive deeper into Cloud Security Fundamentals.
This week focuses on securing AWS cloud environments ‚Äî IAM, network security, storage encryption, and monitoring.
It‚Äôs critical because almost every DevOps/DevSecOps role in 2025 expects you to understand cloud security misconfigurations (the #1 cause of breaches).

üìÖ Week 32: Cloud Security Foundations (AWS Focus)
üéØ Goal
- Learn IAM best practices, network security, encryption in AWS.
- Practice securing S3, EC2, VPCs.
- Use AWS security services (GuardDuty, CloudTrail, Config).
- Deliver a Secure AWS Environment Project repo.

üîπ Day 1 ‚Üí IAM Security Foundations
Topics
- IAM basics recap ‚Üí Users, Groups, Roles, Policies.
- Best practices:
	- Principle of least privilege.
	- Avoid root account usage.
	- MFA for all users.
- IAM Roles for EC2, Lambda.
Practice
- Create IAM role with least privilege ‚Üí attach to EC2.
- Enable MFA for IAM user.
- Generate IAM policy that denies wildcards (*:*).
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è aws-iam-security-demo/ ‚Üí IAM role + MFA + least-privilege policy repo.
Interview Qs
- Difference between IAM Role vs IAM Policy?
- Why is least privilege important?

üîπ Day 2 ‚Üí S3 Security
Topics
- S3 encryption ‚Üí SSE-S3, SSE-KMS, client-side.
- Bucket policies vs IAM policies.
- Public access block settings.
- Preventing data leaks (common interview trap).
Practice
- Create secure S3 bucket:
	- Default encryption enabled (SSE-KMS).
	- Block public access.
	- Bucket policy allowing access only from specific VPC endpoint.
- Try uploading from unauthorized client ‚Üí denied.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è aws-s3-security-demo/ ‚Üí Secure bucket with encryption + restricted policy.
Interview Qs
- How do you prevent accidental public access in S3?
- Difference between SSE-S3 and SSE-KMS?

üîπ Day 3 ‚Üí VPC & Network Security
Topics
- VPC components recap: Subnets, Route Tables, IGW, NAT, Security Groups, NACLs.
- Security concepts:
	- Public vs Private subnets.
	- Security Groups vs NACLs.
	- Flow Logs.
Practice
- Create VPC with:
	- Public + private subnets.
	- EC2 in private subnet (internet via NAT).
	- Security Groups restricting SSH to your IP only.
	- NACL blocking all traffic except HTTPS.
- Enable VPC Flow Logs ‚Üí send to CloudWatch.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è aws-vpc-security-demo/ ‚Üí Terraform/CloudFormation templates for secure VPC.
