Week 36 builds on your SIEM + SOAR foundations (Week 35) and takes you into Red vs Blue Drills + Chaos Security Engineering.
This week, you‚Äôll simulate real-world attacks (Red Team) and practice detecting + responding (Blue Team) with your SIEM/SOAR setup.
This is next-level interview gold because you‚Äôll be able to say: ‚ÄúI‚Äôve simulated real attacks, built detections, and automated responses.‚Äù üíØ

üìÖ Week 36: Red vs Blue Drills + Chaos Security Engineering
üéØ Goal
- Simulate real-world attack techniques using MITRE ATT&CK framework.
- Detect attacks via logs in ELK / Wazuh / Loki.
- Practice Blue Team (defense) + Red Team (attack) drills.
- Apply Chaos Security Engineering (deliberate failure injection for security).
- Capstone ‚Üí End-to-End Attack + Detect + Respond pipeline.

üîπ Day 1 ‚Üí MITRE ATT&CK & Adversary Simulation
Topics
- MITRE ATT&CK ‚Üí framework of tactics & techniques (Recon ‚Üí Exploitation ‚Üí Persistence).
- Red vs Blue Teams ‚Üí Offensive (attackers) vs Defensive (defenders).
- Tools: Atomic Red Team, Caldera, Metasploit basics.
Practice
- Install Atomic Red Team ‚Üí run basic simulations:
	- Credential Dumping.
	- Privilege Escalation.
- Collect logs in ELK.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è mitre-attack-simulation/ ‚Üí Repo with MITRE ATT&CK lab notes + detection queries.
Interview Qs
- What is MITRE ATT&CK?
- How do you simulate adversary techniques in a safe lab?

üîπ Day 2 ‚Üí Red Team Drills (Kubernetes & Cloud)
Topics
- Common Kubernetes attacks:
	- Privileged Pods.
	- Exposed Dashboard.
	- Secret theft.
- Cloud attack scenarios:
	- Public S3 bucket.
	- Stolen IAM keys.
	- EC2 crypto mining.
Practice
- Deploy a privileged Pod ‚Üí try accessing host /etc/passwd.
- Simulate IAM brute force attack (test GuardDuty detection).
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è redteam-k8s-aws-drills/ ‚Üí Scripts for simulating misconfigurations + attacks.
Interview Qs
- How do attackers exploit K8s misconfigurations?
- What are common AWS attack scenarios?

üîπ Day 3 ‚Üí Blue Team Detection (Log Hunting)
Topics
- Threat detection using logs (SIEM queries).
- Writing detection rules for:
	- Suspicious IAM API calls.
	- Privileged Pod creation.
	- Failed SSH brute force attempts.
- MITRE mapping ‚Üí Detection Coverage Matrix.
Practice
- Write Kibana queries for ‚ÄúCreateUser‚Äù in IAM.
- Detect anomalous login attempts in K8s audit logs.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è blueteam-detection-rules/ ‚Üí Repo with SIEM queries + rules mapped to MITRE ATT&CK.
Interview Qs
- How do you detect a brute-force attack in logs?
- What‚Äôs the difference between detection vs prevention?

üîπ Day 4 ‚Üí Chaos Security Engineering
Topics
- What is Chaos Engineering? (Netflix Chaos Monkey).
- Chaos for Security ‚Üí simulate failures & attacks intentionally.
- Tools: Chaos Mesh, LitmusChaos.
Practice
- Install Chaos Mesh in Minikube.
- Run Chaos experiments:
	- Kill a security logging agent Pod ‚Üí verify resiliency.
	- Introduce latency in API calls ‚Üí check monitoring response.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è chaos-security-lab/ ‚Üí Repo with chaos experiments for security observability.
Interview Qs
- What is Chaos Security Engineering?
- Why inject controlled failures in security monitoring systems?

üîπ Day 5 ‚Üí Automated Incident Response Drills
Topics
- Integrating SOAR (Shuffle) with Red/Blue drills.
- Auto-remediation playbooks:
	- Disable IAM user after suspicious API calls.
	- Auto-delete privileged Pod.
	- Block malicious IP in Security Group.
Practice
- Trigger simulated attack ‚Üí verify SOAR playbook auto-remediates.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è soar-incident-drills/ ‚Üí Repo with SOAR playbooks linked to Red Team simulations.
Interview Qs
- What‚Äôs the benefit of automated response in incident handling?
- Example: How would you auto-contain a compromised EC2 instance?

üîπ Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Red vs Blue Battle Lab
Project ‚Üí ‚ÄúDevSecOps Cyber Range: Attack ‚Üí Detect ‚Üí Respond‚Äù
- Workflow:
	- Red Team ‚Üí Simulate AWS + K8s attack.
	- Blue Team ‚Üí Detect via SIEM dashboards & rules.
	- SOAR ‚Üí Auto-remediate attack.
	- Chaos Security ‚Üí Inject failure to test detection resiliency.
- Deliverables:
	- Repo ‚Üí red-vs-blue-cyberrange/.
