Week 37 takes everything you‚Äôve built (Kubernetes, Cloud Security, Incident Response, Red vs Blue drills) and moves into Container Security (Deep Dive).
This week focuses on securing containers at every layer ‚Üí build, runtime, and orchestration. You‚Äôll cover industry-leading tools like Trivy, Clair, Falco, Sysdig, AppArmor, SELinux, seccomp and even container escape scenarios. This is highly interview-relevant since recruiters LOVE asking about Docker/K8s security.

üìÖ Week 37: Container Security (Build ‚Üí Runtime ‚Üí Orchestration)
üéØ Goal
- Learn container attack surfaces (supply chain, runtime, orchestration).
- Secure container images with scanning (Trivy, Clair).
- Apply runtime protections (Falco, Sysdig, seccomp, AppArmor, SELinux).
- Detect + respond to container escape attempts.
- Deliver a Container Security Lab Project repo.

üîπ Day 1 ‚Üí Container Security Fundamentals
Topics
- Container attack surfaces:
	- Image vulnerabilities.
	- Insecure registries.
	- Privileged containers.
	- Kernel exploits.
- Shared kernel model ‚Üí why containers are ‚Äúlightweight VMs but not VMs.‚Äù
- Seccomp, AppArmor, SELinux ‚Üí overview.
Practice
- Run Docker container as root ‚Üí explore risks.
- Run container with --privileged ‚Üí try accessing host.
- Inspect container capabilities with capsh --print.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è container-security-basics/ ‚Üí Demos of privileged vs restricted containers.
Interview Qs
- What‚Äôs the difference between VM isolation and container isolation?
- Why is running containers as root risky?

üîπ Day 2 ‚Üí Image Scanning with Trivy & Clair
Topics
- Image vulnerabilities ‚Üí CVEs.
- Scanners: Trivy, Clair, Grype (compare).
- Integration into CI/CD.
Practice
- Run trivy image nginx:latest.
- Scan Flask app Docker image.
- Export report as JSON ‚Üí fail build on HIGH CVEs.
- Try Clair in local Docker registry.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è container-image-scan-lab/ ‚Üí Repo with Trivy + Clair scan reports integrated in Jenkins.
Interview Qs
- What‚Äôs the difference between Trivy and Clair?
- How do you enforce image scanning in pipelines?

üîπ Day 3 ‚Üí Runtime Security with Falco & Sysdig
Topics
- Runtime monitoring ‚Üí detect suspicious syscalls.
- Falco rules (file writes, exec, privilege escalation).
- Sysdig for forensic container analysis.
Practice
- Install Falco in Minikube.
- Trigger Falco alerts (exec into pod, write to /etc).
- Use Sysdig to capture container activity ‚Üí analyze sysdig -p"%evt.type %proc.name".
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è falco-sysdig-lab/ ‚Üí Repo with Falco rules + Sysdig capture files.
Interview Qs
- How does Falco detect threats?
- Difference between Falco and Sysdig?

üîπ Day 4 ‚Üí Seccomp, AppArmor & SELinux
Topics
- Seccomp profiles ‚Üí block dangerous syscalls.
- AppArmor profiles ‚Üí restrict filesystem/network access.
- SELinux policies ‚Üí labeling, enforcement.
Practice
- Create custom Seccomp profile ‚Üí deny chmod.
- Apply AppArmor profile to Nginx container.
- Enable SELinux enforcing mode in CentOS ‚Üí run restricted container.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è container-seccomp-apparmor/ ‚Üí Profiles + demo scripts.
Interview Qs
- Difference between Seccomp, AppArmor, SELinux?
- How do you enforce least privilege in container runtime?

üîπ Day 5 ‚Üí Container Escape & Mitigations
Topics
- Container escape techniques:
	- Privileged containers.
	- Volume mounts (/var/run/docker.sock).
	- Kernel exploits (Dirty COW).
- Defense-in-depth: rootless containers, namespaces, cgroups.
Practice
- Run container with -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock ‚Üí show host control risk.
- Run container with root ‚Üí attempt privilege escalation.
- Harden: rootless Podman / Docker.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è container-escape-lab/ ‚Üí Repo with demos of insecure vs hardened configs.
Interview Qs
- How can attackers escape a container?
- What‚Äôs the risk of mounting the Docker socket?

üîπ Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Container Security Lab
Project ‚Üí ‚ÄúContainer Security End-to-End‚Äù
- Features:
	- Image scanning (Trivy, Clair).
	- Runtime monitoring (Falco, Sysdig).
	- Seccomp + AppArmor profiles.
	- Escape simulation ‚Üí hardened containers with rootless Docker.
Deliverables
- Repo ‚Üí container-security-lab/
- Scanning reports, Falco configs, security profiles.
- README + security architecture diagram.
Interview Drill
- Walk me through how you secure containers in build ‚Üí runtime ‚Üí orchestration.
- How do you detect container escape attempts?

