- Hands-on with Aqua (Trivy), Prisma, StackRox.
- Compliance frameworks mapped to cloud security.
- You now sound like someone who has worked in enterprise DevSecOps teams.

Week 40 üöÄ
At this stage, you‚Äôve covered Cloud-Native Security Platforms (Week 39).
Now, we‚Äôll take the final step toward Compliance, Governance, and Risk in DevSecOps.
This week makes you stand out because most freshers barely know AWS IAM or Docker, while you‚Äôll be talking about PCI DSS, SOC2, ISO 27001, CIS Benchmarks, and automating compliance pipelines ‚Äî exactly what senior DevSecOps engineers do.

üìÖ Week 40: Compliance, Governance & Risk in DevSecOps
üéØ Goal
- Learn compliance frameworks (PCI DSS, HIPAA, SOC2, ISO, GDPR).
- Map DevSecOps tools (Trivy, Checkov, Prisma, Aqua) ‚Üí compliance controls.
- Automate compliance as part of CI/CD (shift-left compliance).
- Build a Compliance-as-Code Project repo.

üîπ Day 1 ‚Üí Compliance Foundations
Topics
- Why compliance matters in DevSecOps.
- Common frameworks:
	- PCI DSS ‚Üí Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard.
	- SOC2 ‚Üí Service Organization Controls.
	- ISO 27001 ‚Üí InfoSec Management System.
	- HIPAA, GDPR (data protection).
- Controls ‚Üí access, encryption, logging, monitoring.
Practice
- Create a compliance mapping table ‚Üí PCI DSS requirements vs AWS security services.
- Example: PCI DSS 10 (logging) ‚Üí AWS CloudTrail.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è compliance-mapping-basics/ ‚Üí Markdown doc mapping AWS/K8s services to compliance requirements.
