üîπ Day 3 ‚Üí Compliance-as-Code (Checkov, OPA, Conftest)
Topics
- What is Compliance-as-Code?
- Tools: Checkov, OPA, Conftest ‚Üí enforce compliance in CI/CD.
- Example policies:
	- No public S3 buckets.
	- All resources must have tags.
	- Pods must have resource limits.
Practice
- Write Checkov rules for Terraform ‚Üí fail build if S3 is public.
- Write OPA policy ‚Üí deny Pods without labels.
- Integrate with GitHub Actions pipeline.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è compliance-as-code-lab/ ‚Üí repo with Checkov + OPA rules in CI/CD.
Interview Qs
- What‚Äôs the difference between Security-as-Code and Compliance-as-Code?
- How do you enforce compliance early (shift-left)?

üîπ Day 4 ‚Üí Cloud Governance & Risk
Topics
- Cloud Governance ‚Üí ensuring cost, security, compliance alignment.
- Risk management in cloud: misconfigs, insider threats, data leaks.
- Tools: AWS Config, Security Hub, Prisma Cloud.
Practice
- Create AWS Config rules ‚Üí
	- Deny public S3.
	- Enforce encryption on EBS.
- Test with non-compliant resources ‚Üí see findings.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è aws-governance-lab/ ‚Üí repo with AWS Config + governance rules.
