Patch Add-On Sheet for Weeks 37‚Äì40.
This is like a side quest list ‚Äî not mandatory for the flow, but highly recommended if you want to sound like a 2‚Äì3 year experienced DevSecOps engineer in interviews.

üìå Patch Add-On Sheet (Weeks 37‚Äì40)

üê≥ Week 37 Add-Ons ‚Üí Container Security
üîπ Docker Bench for Security
- Tool: docker-bench-security ‚Üí checks for Docker daemon, host, and container misconfigs.
- Practice: Run on local Docker host, fix issues.
- Mini-Project ‚Üí docker-bench-lab/: reports + remediation notes.
- Interview Q: What‚Äôs Docker Bench, and how does it differ from Trivy?
üîπ Image Signing & Trust
- Basics of Docker Content Trust / Notary v2.
- Sign and verify images before pushing.
- Interview Q: How does image signing prevent supply chain attacks?
üîπ Linux Namespace Isolation
- Deep dive into pid, net, mnt, ipc, uts, and user namespaces.
- Run unshare commands ‚Üí test namespace isolation.
- Interview Q: What‚Äôs the role of user namespaces in container security?

‚ò∏Ô∏è Week 38 Add-Ons ‚Üí Kubernetes Hardening
üîπ PodSecurity Admission (PSA)
- Replacement for PodSecurityPolicy (deprecated).
- Levels: Privileged, Baseline, Restricted.
- Practice: Enable restricted PSA ‚Üí try deploying privileged Pod.
üîπ Kubernetes Secrets Security
- Use Sealed Secrets (Bitnami) ‚Üí encrypt secrets in Git.
- Use External Secrets Operator ‚Üí fetch from AWS Secrets Manager.
- Interview Q: Why shouldn‚Äôt you store Secrets directly in Git?
üîπ Multi-Tenancy Security
- Namespace isolation with RBAC + NetworkPolicies.
- Best practices for multi-team clusters.
- Interview Q: How do you secure multi-tenant workloads on the same cluster?

‚òÅÔ∏è Week 39 Add-Ons ‚Üí CNSPs
üîπ Wiz & Orca Security Awareness
- These are the market leaders (2025).
- Feature: agentless scanning of cloud accounts.
- Even without hands-on ‚Üí read whitepapers + dashboards.
- Interview Q: What‚Äôs the difference between Wiz/Orca and Prisma/Aqua?
üîπ Runtime Drift Detection
- CNSPs detect when a running container has binaries not in original image.
- Example: /bin/bash appears in runtime but wasn‚Äôt in Dockerfile.
- Interview Q: What is runtime drift detection, and why is it important?
üîπ Comparative Matrix (Open Source vs Enterprise)
- Table comparing:
	- Trivy vs Aqua.
	- OPA/Kyverno vs Prisma.
	- Falco vs StackRox runtime detection.
- Mini-Project ‚Üí cnsp-comparison-notes/: Markdown table.

üìú Week 40 Add-Ons ‚Üí Compliance, Governance & Risk
üîπ SOX Compliance (Financial Systems)
- Focuses on audit trails + financial record protection.
- Practice: Map SOX controls ‚Üí CloudTrail + GuardDuty.
- Interview Q: What‚Äôs the difference between SOX and SOC2?
üîπ GDPR & CCPA Awareness
- GDPR ‚Üí EU data protection, ‚ÄúRight to be Forgotten.‚Äù
- CCPA ‚Üí California data privacy rights.
- Practice: Write short note ‚Üí how encryption + access logs help compliance.
- Interview Q: How would you make an app GDPR-compliant?
üîπ Continuous Audit Reporting
- Export compliance reports ‚Üí ELK or Splunk for auditors.
- Practice: In CI/CD, export Checkov/Prowler reports ‚Üí store in S3.
- Interview Q: How do you prove continuous compliance to auditors?

