Week 41.
By this point, you‚Äôve covered Container Security, K8s Hardening, CNSPs, and Compliance. Now it‚Äôs time to step into Infrastructure Security & Zero Trust ‚Äî a critical area where DevSecOps and Security Engineering overlap.
This week will prepare you to talk like a Cloud Security Engineer while still staying on the DevSecOps track.

üìÖ Week 41: Infrastructure Security & Zero Trust
üéØ Goal
- Learn Zero Trust Architecture and how it applies to cloud & Kubernetes.
- Secure infrastructure with Identity, Access, Encryption, and Monitoring.
- Explore beyond IAM: service identities, workload identity federation.
- Build a Zero Trust Infra Security Lab repo.

üîπ Day 1 ‚Üí Zero Trust Fundamentals
Topics
- Zero Trust principles:
	- Never trust, always verify.
	- Least privilege.
	- Continuous verification.
- Zero Trust in Cloud & K8s.
- Tools: Istio mTLS, SPIFFE/SPIRE.
Practice
- Draw Zero Trust architecture for a 3-tier cloud app.
- Enable Istio mTLS between services.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è zero-trust-basics/ ‚Üí Architecture diagram + Istio mTLS demo.
Interview Qs
- What is Zero Trust?
- How is it different from traditional perimeter security?

üîπ Day 2 ‚Üí Identity & Access Security
Topics
- Workload Identity Federation.
- Service-to-service authentication with SPIFFE/SPIRE.
- IAM hardening beyond basics: conditional IAM, service accounts.
Practice
- Deploy SPIRE in Minikube.
- Assign service identity to Pods.
- Enforce Pod-to-Pod authentication via SPIRE.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è workload-identity-lab/ ‚Üí SPIRE demo repo with Pod identities.
Interview Qs
- Difference between IAM roles vs SPIFFE IDs?
- How does workload identity improve security?

üîπ Day 3 ‚Üí Infrastructure Encryption & Secrets
Topics
- Data-in-transit ‚Üí TLS everywhere.
- Data-at-rest ‚Üí KMS, envelope encryption.
- Secrets management ‚Üí Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, External Secrets.
Practice
- Deploy HashiCorp Vault on Minikube.
- Store DB password in Vault ‚Üí retrieve via External Secrets Operator.
- Encrypt an S3 bucket with KMS CMK.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è vault-secrets-lab/ ‚Üí Vault + External Secrets + S3 encryption setup.
Interview Qs
- What‚Äôs the difference between KMS and Vault?
- Why shouldn‚Äôt you store secrets in ConfigMaps?

üîπ Day 4 ‚Üí Network Security in Zero Trust
Topics
- Microsegmentation: service-level firewalls.
- Network Policies in K8s (restrict east-west traffic).
- Service Mesh for zero trust networking.
Practice
- Apply NetworkPolicy ‚Üí only frontend can talk to backend.
- Deny all traffic except whitelisted namespaces.
- Verify with kubectl exec curl.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è zero-trust-networking/ ‚Üí NetworkPolicies + test cases.
Interview Qs
- What‚Äôs the difference between NetworkPolicy and Security Groups?
- How does Istio extend Zero Trust networking?

üîπ Day 5 ‚Üí Monitoring & Continuous Verification
Topics
- Continuous verification in Zero Trust.
- Detecting policy violations in real-time.
- Tools: OPA, Falco, Security Hub.
Practice
- Write OPA policy ‚Üí deny root containers.
- Falco alert ‚Üí Pod attempted root escalation.
- Send violations to Slack.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è zero-trust-monitoring/ ‚Üí OPA + Falco + Slack integration.
Interview Qs
- How do you continuously enforce Zero Trust?
- What‚Äôs the role of OPA in Zero Trust security?

üîπ Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Zero Trust Security Lab
Project ‚Üí ‚ÄúZero Trust Cloud-Native Infrastructure‚Äù
- Features:
	- SPIRE ‚Üí workload identity.
	- Vault ‚Üí secrets management.
	- Istio ‚Üí mTLS.
	- KMS ‚Üí data encryption.
	- NetworkPolicies ‚Üí service-level isolation.
	- OPA/Falco ‚Üí continuous verification.
Deliverables
- Repo ‚Üí zero-trust-infra-lab/
- YAMLs, Vault configs, SPIRE setup, OPA/Falco rules.
- Architecture diagram + README.
Interview Drill
