üìÖ Week 43: Secure CI/CD Pipelines (DevSecOps in Practice)
üéØ Goal
- Master secure CI/CD practices.
- Integrate scanning (SAST, DAST, IaC, Secrets) into pipelines.
- Automate compliance + policy enforcement.
- Deliver a ‚ÄúSecure CI/CD Framework‚Äù repo.

üîπ Day 1 ‚Üí Secure CI/CD Foundations
Topics
- CI/CD security layers:
	- Code ‚Üí SAST (Static Application Security Testing).
	- Dependencies ‚Üí SBOM + image scanning.
	- IaC ‚Üí Terraform/Helm scanning.
	- Runtime ‚Üí K8s policies.
- Shift-left security in DevSecOps.
Practice
- Build GitHub Actions pipeline:
	- Run Trivy for Docker image scan.
	- Run Checkov for Terraform scan.
	- Fail build if HIGH CVEs or policy violations.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è secure-cicd-basics/ ‚Üí Secure pipeline demo with Trivy + Checkov.
Interview Qs
