üîπ Day 5 ‚Üí Policy Enforcement in Pipelines
Topics
- Policy-as-Code ‚Üí enforce compliance before deployment.
- Tools: OPA Conftest, Kyverno.
- Use cases:
	- Only signed images allowed.
	- Pods must have limits.
	- Terraform must not expose resources.
Practice
- Write Conftest policy ‚Üí fail build if Terraform exposes S3.
- Write Kyverno policy ‚Üí fail deploy if Pod runs as root.
Mini-Project
‚û°Ô∏è cicd-policy-enforcement/ ‚Üí Policies integrated with GitHub Actions.
Interview Qs
- How is OPA different from Kyverno?
- Why use policy enforcement in pipelines?

üîπ Day 6 ‚Üí Capstone Project: Secure CI/CD Framework
Project ‚Üí ‚ÄúEnterprise Secure CI/CD Framework‚Äù
- Features:
	- Secrets ‚Üí Vault + SOPS.
	- Scanning ‚Üí Trivy, Checkov, Grype, SonarQube, ZAP.
	- IaC enforcement ‚Üí Checkov, Conftest.
	- K8s enforcement ‚Üí Kyverno.
	- GitHub Actions pipeline ‚Üí fail on violations.
Deliverables
