- You‚Äôll sound like a Cloud Security Engineer + DevSecOps hybrid ‚Üí fresher with 2‚Äì3 yrs level skills.


Patch Add-On Sheet (Weeks 45‚Äì48) that layers extra depth, STAR storytelling prep, troubleshooting drills, and high-impact interview practice onto your existing daily roadmap.
This isn‚Äôt a replacement for the roadmap ‚Äî it‚Äôs the booster pack to make your portfolio + interviews bulletproof.

üõ†Ô∏è Patch Add-On Sheet (Weeks 45‚Äì48)

üîπ Week 45 ‚Äì Chaos Engineering & Resilience Testing
üéØ Add-Ons
- STAR Practice (Behavioral):
  
  Q: Tell me about a time when your monitoring system failed.
  
   ‚Üí Story: Use your chaos experiment where Falco/Prometheus went down. Highlight: Situation (chaos test), Task (validate resilience), Action (built redeploy strategy), Result (no alerting gaps).
- Troubleshooting Drill:
  
   Simulate Vault downtime ‚Üí App crash ‚Üí Debug logs ‚Üí Apply failover secrets ‚Üí Record step-by-step troubleshooting playbook.
- Extra Tools to Try: Gremlin (SaaS chaos), Chaos Toolkit.
- Portfolio Bonus: Add ‚ÄúFailure Catalog‚Äù (list of chaos experiments, results, lessons learned).

üîπ Week 46 ‚Äì Red Teaming & Adversary Emulation
üéØ Add-Ons
- STAR Practice (Technical Behavioral):
  
  Q: Describe a time you thought like an attacker.
  
   ‚Üí Story: Pick AWS Pacu + GuardDuty detection. Emphasize offense-to-defense mindset.
- Troubleshooting Drill:
  
   Run Atomic Red Team test (privilege escalation). ‚Üí If SIEM detection fails, tune Falco rule or Kibana query. ‚Üí Document ‚ÄúDetection Gaps & Fixes‚Äù in repo.
- Extra Tools to Try: BloodHound (AD attacks), Prowler (AWS security scanner).
- Portfolio Bonus: MITRE ATT&CK Mapping Matrix ‚Üí Add heatmap of techniques tested vs detected.

üîπ Week 47 ‚Äì Purple Teaming & Detection Engineering
üéØ Add-Ons
- STAR Practice (Teamwork Behavioral):
  
  Q: How do you collaborate with security and operations teams?
  
   ‚Üí Story: Purple Team exercise ‚Üí you ran attacks, tuned detections, created playbooks ‚Üí reduced false positives.
- Troubleshooting Drill:
  
   Inject false positives in detection rule (too many alerts). ‚Üí Refine thresholding + enrichment. ‚Üí Document before/after false-positive ratio.
- Extra Tools to Try: Sigma (rule format), Shuffle SOAR.
- Portfolio Bonus: Deliver a ‚ÄúDetection Playbook Notebook‚Äù repo ‚Üí queries, false-positive tuning notes, playbooks.

üîπ Week 48 ‚Äì Multi-Cloud Security
üéØ Add-Ons
- STAR Practice (Cloud Security):
  
  Q: How do you secure workloads across multiple cloud providers?
  
   ‚Üí Story: Multi-Cloud Lab ‚Üí IAM differences, logging centralization, compliance mapping.
- Troubleshooting Drill:
  
   Break scenario ‚Üí Enable public bucket in AWS, Azure, GCP. Detect ‚Üí Fix with Config/Policy/Validator. Document as ‚ÄúMulti-Cloud Compliance Runbook.‚Äù
- Extra Tools to Try: Fugue (multi-cloud compliance), Wiz (cloud security posture management).
- Portfolio Bonus: Add a Comparison Cheat Sheet repo ‚Üí IAM, Networking, KMS, Logging differences between AWS/Azure/GCP.

‚úÖ End of Patch Add-On (Weeks 45‚Äì48) Deliverables
